== Verb ==
'''tish'''

# To blather pretentiously; either a) to say a simple thing with unnecessarily elevated language, or b)to ramble pedantically (and often unintelligibly) about an intellectual subject.
#: ''The guide was tolerable until we reached the left wing of the museum; then, after proclaiming it was her favorite section, she tished on impressionism for a half hour.''


== Etymology ==

From the character Petratishkovna "Tish" Katsufrakis, intellectual 13-year-old girl on the Disney cartoon, "The Weekenders"; verb coined by her friends in the episode, "To Tish"